  "prompt": "When and how did WWI start and end?",
  "response": "World War I (WWI) began on **July 28, 1914**, and ended on **November 11, 1918**. Here\u2019s a summary of its start and conclusion:\n\n### **How It Started:**\n1. **Immediate Cause:** The assassination of **Archduke Franz Ferdinand** of Austria-Hungary by **Gavrilo Princip**, a Bosnian Serb nationalist, on **June 28, 1914**, in Sarajevo.\n2. **Escalation of Tensions:** Austria-Hungary, backed by Germany, issued an ultimatum to Serbia, which Serbia did not fully accept. This led Austria-Hungary to declare war on Serbia on **July 28, 1914**.\n3. **Alliances and Mobilization:** The conflict quickly escalated due to a web of alliances. Russia mobilized to support Serbia, Germany declared war on Russia and France, and Britain entered the war after Germany invaded Belgium.\n\n### **How It Ended:**\n1. **U.S. Entry:** The United States entered the war on **April 6, 1917**, after Germany\u2019s unrestricted submarine warfare and the sinking of American ships.\n2. **Allied Advancements:** By 1918, the Allies (including Britain, France, and the U.S.) gained momentum against the Central Powers (Germany, Austria-Hungary, the Ottoman Empire, and Bulgaria).\n3. **Armistice:** Germany signed an armistice agreement on **November 11, 1918**, effectively ending the fighting.\n4. **Treaty of Versailles:** The war officially concluded with the signing of the **Treaty of Versailles** on **June 28, 1919**, which imposed harsh terms on Germany.\n\n### **Legacy:**\nWWI, often called the \"Great War,\" resulted in unprecedented destruction, with millions of military and civilian casualties. It reshaped global borders, dismantled empires, and set the stage for World War II.",
